This is the powerful *software* that runs on your computer. It's the "engine" that does the actual version control work â€“ tracking changes, managing history, etc.
Git commands are used in terminal.
Git's three states are Working Directory, Staging Area and Local Repository.
Key commands: git init, git clone, git status, git add, git commit, git log.
One of the best practices is to commit frequently with clear, concise messages.
